title: What was the number one song in April 1968? - Quora

response.answer_text: If you mean here in the United States (as other countries have music charts too 🙂). then yes, I know it. For the first week of April (actually March 31st through April 6th, it was 4th and final week “Sittin’ On The Dock Of The Bay” by Otis Redding was #1. Then from April 7th to May 11th, it was “Honey” by male Adult Contemporary singer Bobby Goldsboro, 5 weeks on top. 👨←- Looks like him too 😃 LOL.
